He explains the different results obtained by the applicants (ie, according to whether the latter were using the usernames and passwords provided by the respondents to the applicant's counsel or were using other user names and passwords) by reference to three matters, namely: (a) the presence of the 397 Infosafe MSDSs which were inadvertently left on the Tennessee server, and which were not accessible "on the copy of The Collection accessed via the other website";
